    "summary": "MR Methods development for neuroscience research, with strong focus on ultra-high field MRI. \n\nPulse sequence development for BOLD-, perfusion and blood volume weighted fMRI for 1.5, 3, 7 and 9.4T human MRI; all Siemens\nLover of echo-train pulse sequences including multi-echo EPI, 3D EPI, 3D GRASE, TSE, HASTE\nParallel RF transmission in ways that are actually useful\nDevelopment of artefact correction strategies, including distortion correction, EPI ghost correction at 7T, bipolar RF excitation, ...\nParallel imaging techniques and image reconstruction prototyping in Matlab. \nnon-Cartesian acquisition\nMR recon using DL/NN approaches\nBOLD biophysics\n\n",
